1
00:00:41,479 --> 00:00:42,399
This informant

2
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:43,920
Can we even trust him?

3
00:00:44,079 --> 00:00:45,280
What's his identity?

4
00:00:45,399 --> 00:00:46,359
Who is he?

5
00:00:46,359 --> 00:00:48,159
Shouldn't colleagues share that much?

6
00:00:49,079 --> 00:00:50,520
You want to know who he is?

7
00:00:51,079 --> 00:00:52,280
Did you even use your brain?

8
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:54,159
Do you want him dead?

9
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:55,840
What's that supposed to mean?

10
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:58,280
All these years,

11
00:00:58,799 --> 00:01:00,079
us brothers in the Major Crimes Unit,

12
00:01:00,079 --> 00:01:01,640
how much work have we done for you?

13
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:03,079
How many of us have died?

14
00:01:03,079 --> 00:01:03,840
And you talk to me like this?

15
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:05,400
Have you no humanity, Chen Jiadong?

16
00:01:05,719 --> 00:01:07,359
Liu Zhenfeng, I'm trying to reason with you.

17
00:01:07,719 --> 00:01:09,760
How many of my brothers have died?

18
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:11,000
I remember every single one.

19
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,280
Then tell me, who is it?

20
00:01:12,719 --> 00:01:14,359
Remember, every time we went out on a call,

21
00:01:14,359 --> 00:01:15,159
we were all wondering,

22
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:17,319
who exactly is the mole in the force?

23
00:01:17,959 --> 00:01:19,280
I remember telling you,

24
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,519
I don't want to see anyone else die.

25
00:01:20,519 --> 00:01:21,760
I want to take it slow,

26
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:24,359
so we can uproot Heyisheng completely.

27
00:01:24,359 --> 00:01:26,000
Chen Jiadong, let me tell you,

28
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:28,280
the mole is inside your Anti-Triad Unit.

29
00:01:28,359 --> 00:01:29,000
Is it you?

30
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:29,680
Is it you?

31
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:30,760
It's me.

32
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:32,439
You said it yourself.

33
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:41,159
Sit down.

34
00:01:57,799 --> 00:01:59,879
I think at this stage

35
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,200
we should focus all our efforts

36
00:02:01,359 --> 00:02:04,000
on the case of Wang Danni's fall itself

37
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,200
Let's not branch out too much for now

38
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:09,120
There's one thing I've never understood

39
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,800
The victim, Wang Danni,

40
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,960
and the prime suspect,

41
00:02:13,719 --> 00:02:15,080
Liang Zhiqiang,

42
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,520
how did the two of them meet?

43
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,639
A-Qiang

44
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,080
Come on, dig in, dig in

45
00:02:20,159 --> 00:02:21,439
These are all my signature dishes

46
00:02:21,919 --> 00:02:22,919
Thank you, Uncle Xiang

47
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,159
So many dishes

48
00:02:24,159 --> 00:02:25,000
Can we finish it all?

49
00:02:25,159 --> 00:02:26,879
We can, we can

50
00:02:26,879 --> 00:02:27,879
There's one more person coming

51
00:02:30,439 --> 00:02:31,280
I'm back

52
00:02:33,639 --> 00:02:34,159
You're back

53
00:02:34,319 --> 00:02:35,280
Let me introduce you

54
00:02:35,719 --> 00:02:36,759
This is Liang Zhiqiang

55
00:02:36,759 --> 00:02:37,599
Call him Brother Qiang

56
00:02:41,039 --> 00:02:42,039
Just call me A-Qiang

57
00:02:42,039 --> 00:02:43,120
This is my daughter, Danni

58
00:02:43,319 --> 00:02:44,240
Come, come, sit down

59
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,360
You have the three highs,

60
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,400
eating food this greasy,

61
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,280
are you trying to kill yourself?

62
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,479
Just one meal to satisfy the craving

63
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,599
Brother Qiang is in a gang?

64
00:02:53,919 --> 00:02:54,680
No

65
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,080
I quit that long ago

66
00:02:57,159 --> 00:02:58,479
Quit that long ago

67
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:00,719
Quit long ago means you were in it before

68
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,680
I was young and foolish back then

69
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,039
Young and foolish back then

70
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,960
Don't be so defensive, come on

71
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,360
Always acting like you're interrogating someone

72
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:11,840
I've known Brother Qiang for twenty years

73
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,879
I know exactly what kind of man he is

74
00:03:14,439 --> 00:03:15,159
Oh, you know?

75
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:17,280
Then do you know where he works now?

76
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,400
Of course I do

77
00:03:19,879 --> 00:03:20,680
Doing manual labor

78
00:03:20,719 --> 00:03:21,520
Manual labor?

79
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,400
But it didn't work out

80
00:03:23,759 --> 00:03:24,759
Didn't work out

81
00:03:25,319 --> 00:03:26,120
I'm not doing it anymore

82
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,360
Not doing it anymore

83
00:03:28,479 --> 00:03:30,080
Not doing it anymore? Great

84
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:31,520
Come work at my flower shop then

85
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:32,639
I've got an open position here

86
00:03:32,639 --> 00:03:33,719
Are you interested?

87
00:03:35,599 --> 00:03:36,800
Wouldn't that be too much trouble?

88
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,319
No, not at all

89
00:03:38,319 --> 00:03:40,199
Well, room and board are covered here

90
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:41,560
12,000 a month

91
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,199
Just treat this place

92
00:03:43,199 --> 00:03:44,879
like it's your own home

93
00:03:45,199 --> 00:03:46,039
Thank you, Uncle Xiang

94
00:03:48,479 --> 00:03:49,280
Come with me

95
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,199
It's fine, it's fine

96
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,159
Go on, eat

97
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,319
How can you just take in anyone?

98
00:04:01,319 --> 00:04:02,560
He's from the triads

99
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,360
He's not that kind of person

100
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,840
He did run with them when he was young

101
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,080
but it's different now

102
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:09,960
He's turned over a new leaf now

103
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:12,479
Young people always make mistakes

104
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,919
Have you forgotten what happened to Mom?

105
00:04:17,879 --> 00:04:19,399
If you feel sorry for him,

106
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:21,600
buying him a meal is one thing

107
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:25,160
But don't even think about letting him work here

108
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,839
But he's been having a hard time lately

109
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,519
He has no friends and no money

110
00:04:33,279 --> 00:04:35,000
Did you forget he helped us the other day?

111
00:04:36,839 --> 00:04:38,920
Or let's give him just one month

112
00:04:39,399 --> 00:04:40,480
Just one month, all right?

113
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,160
All right

114
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:44,519
Then it's settled

115
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,600
A-Qiang

116
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,519
Come on, dig in, dig in

117
00:04:49,639 --> 00:04:51,120
The food's gone cold

118
00:04:55,959 --> 00:04:57,959
With the three highs, eat a little less

119
00:04:59,519 --> 00:05:00,399
Have more kelp instead

120
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,439
Go on, eat plenty

121
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:07,040
This beef has been sitting for a month

122
00:05:09,759 --> 00:05:11,639
All right, all right, just eat

123
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,360
Danni, eat with us

124
00:05:14,759 --> 00:05:15,199
Here

125
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,759
So spicy

126
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:18,879
Honestly

127
00:05:18,879 --> 00:05:20,160
Here's to prosperity!

128
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,240
Hello

129
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,000
Thank you for your help

130
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,000
Here's our business card

131
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,079
How many times have I told you?

132
00:06:05,079 --> 00:06:05,800
This is a succulent

133
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,040
You can't water it that much

134
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,040
It'll get root rot

135
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:11,480
Look at this

136
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:14,000
Grab a rag and wipe it up, quick

137
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:20,680
And another thing

138
00:06:23,399 --> 00:06:24,319
It's got root rot

139
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,319
Is this your motorcycle?

140
00:06:34,319 --> 00:06:36,000
Yes. Do you like motorcycles?

141
00:06:36,399 --> 00:06:37,160
I do

142
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,519
It's exactly like the one I used to have

143
00:06:47,439 --> 00:06:47,959
Goodbye

144
00:07:03,879 --> 00:07:04,879
Liang Zhiqiang.

145
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,399
Liu Zhenfeng, Major Crimes Unit.

146
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,920
Officer Chen isn't here.

147
00:07:15,439 --> 00:07:16,360
He's not around.

148
00:07:16,399 --> 00:07:17,480
Yeah, he's a busy man.

149
00:07:18,759 --> 00:07:19,360
Arranging flowers?

150
00:07:19,959 --> 00:07:21,160
Didn't know you could do that.

151
00:07:21,839 --> 00:07:22,600
Just picking it up.

152
00:07:23,399 --> 00:07:24,600
Getting used to life outside?

153
00:07:25,079 --> 00:07:26,560
Sure beats being locked up, right?

154
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:29,600
How much do you make a month?

155
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,680
He makes 12,000 a month now.

156
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,000
Room and board included.

157
00:07:35,319 --> 00:07:37,800
Mainly he takes care of the shop,

158
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,040
handles deliveries,

159
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,360
and looks after the customers.

160
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,560
I'm the owner of this shop.

161
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:44,279
Is there something I can help you with?

162
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,240
Hello.

163
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,319
Then you must know

164
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:50,040
he's a released ex-convict, right?

165
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,279
A serious offender.

166
00:07:55,279 --> 00:07:56,360
Did he hide that from you?

167
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:57,639
No, he didn't.

168
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:59,839
We knew when we hired him.

169
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,480
How's he doing these days?

170
00:08:03,839 --> 00:08:04,639
Pretty well.

171
00:08:06,759 --> 00:08:07,439
That's all, then.

172
00:08:09,639 --> 00:08:10,800
Twenty-odd years behind bars.

173
00:08:10,839 --> 00:08:12,519
Finding work isn't easy.

174
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,079
Stay on the right path.

175
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,079
Cherish it.

176
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,560
I will.

177
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:31,040
So...

178
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,879
You were locked up for 20 years.

179
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:39,840
Such a heavy sentence.

180
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,480
You've got blood on your hands.

181
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:44,440
I never killed anyone.

182
00:08:45,799 --> 00:08:47,440
And I don't do that old stuff anymore.

183
00:08:57,399 --> 00:08:58,279
I see.

184
00:08:58,919 --> 00:09:01,159
Thanks to you and Uncle Xiang for taking care of me.

185
00:09:02,799 --> 00:09:04,200
Sorry for the trouble.

186
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,240
I'll be taking my leave.

187
00:09:09,519 --> 00:09:10,720
What is it you think you understand?

188
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,440
Where do you plan on going?

189
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,679
What kind of place do you think this is?

190
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,519
You show up whenever you want,

191
00:09:14,519 --> 00:09:15,399
and leave whenever you want?

192
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,639
This table's a total mess.

193
00:09:19,639 --> 00:09:20,759
We've got customers coming soon.

194
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:21,759
You want to keep this business running or not?

195
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,399
Get back to work already.

196
00:09:29,279 --> 00:09:30,320
Something else?

197
00:09:32,159 --> 00:09:33,840
Just settle my pay for this month.

198
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:34,360
Huh?

199
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,360
12,000.

200
00:09:40,799 --> 00:09:42,360
You just hauled all those flowers,

201
00:09:42,639 --> 00:09:44,240
and you don't even look tired.

202
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,679
Do you work out?

203
00:09:46,399 --> 00:09:48,399
I exercise regularly.

204
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,600
Where are you from, Brother Qiang?

205
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,639
I'm from Chaoshan.

206
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:57,759
You're from Chaoshan?

207
00:09:57,919 --> 00:09:58,360
Yeah.

208
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,279
A Chaoshan native.

209
00:09:59,399 --> 00:10:00,200
A Chaoshan native.

210
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,240
Where in Chaoshan?

211
00:10:01,679 --> 00:10:02,480
Chaoyang.

212
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:05,159
No wonder.

213
00:10:05,159 --> 00:10:06,360
We're from the same hometown.

214
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:16,559
So beautiful.

215
00:10:19,279 --> 00:10:20,200
Oh, right.

216
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:46,639
Where's Xiao Qi?

217
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:47,960
No idea.

218
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,840
Haven't seen him in days.

219
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:51,399
You don't know?

220
00:10:51,559 --> 00:10:53,000
He's working at a nightclub now.

221
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:53,720
See?

222
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,639
I always said he likes hanging around

223
00:10:54,639 --> 00:10:56,320
those shady places.

224
00:10:56,399 --> 00:10:58,600
Maybe he's already run off with someone.

225
00:10:58,679 --> 00:11:00,240
Sister Dandan took such good care of him,

226
00:11:00,279 --> 00:11:01,759
but he's a lost cause.

227
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,720
Don't talk like that.

228
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,519
Maybe he'll land some rich lady one day,

229
00:11:05,639 --> 00:11:07,399
and be way out of our league.

230
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:09,480
Then we'll have to call him Brother Qi.

231
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,039
Had enough laughs yet?

232
00:11:14,759 --> 00:11:15,919
Keep talking nonsense,

233
00:11:15,919 --> 00:11:17,919
and I'll send you to the disciplinary office to explain.

234
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:01,840
Teacher Danni

235
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,080
What are you doing here?

236
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,720
You've got some nerve asking that.

237
00:12:04,759 --> 00:12:05,759
You've been gone for days.

238
00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:08,080
Skipping school to work in a dump like this.

239
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:08,919
Come with me.

240
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:11,200
Teacher, I really do want to drop out.

241
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,279
I just want to make more money.

242
00:12:12,639 --> 00:12:13,679
A place like this is dangerous.

243
00:12:13,679 --> 00:12:14,399
Don't you understand?

244
00:12:14,879 --> 00:12:16,000
What if something happens to you?

245
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:16,840
Let's go.

246
00:12:19,159 --> 00:12:20,679
I was wondering who's making all this fuss.

247
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,639
If it isn't Teacher Danni from the flower shop.

248
00:12:25,759 --> 00:12:27,440
What, here to unwind?

249
00:12:28,639 --> 00:12:30,080
Want me to set you up with some hot guys?

250
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:31,679
Watch your filthy mouth.

251
00:12:31,799 --> 00:12:32,879
Don't be disgusting.

252
00:12:34,399 --> 00:12:35,480
Got your eye on our Xiao Qi?

253
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,679
What nonsense are you spouting?

254
00:12:36,759 --> 00:12:38,320
I'm here to take my student home.

255
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:40,159
He doesn't belong in a hole like this.

256
00:12:42,639 --> 00:12:44,440
I hear his old man is sick.

257
00:12:44,519 --> 00:12:46,519
His older sister is working so hard,

258
00:12:46,519 --> 00:12:47,720
so he came here for a job.

259
00:12:48,519 --> 00:12:49,639
Such a devoted son.

260
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:52,639
But we've signed a contract, you know.

261
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,720
It's all there in black and white.

262
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:55,679
You can't just break the contract.

263
00:12:56,159 --> 00:12:57,799
There are plenty of other places to work.

264
00:12:57,879 --> 00:12:59,399
He shouldn't be at a place like yours.

265
00:13:00,559 --> 00:13:01,639
Even if he has to work,

266
00:13:01,879 --> 00:13:03,600
he can't fall behind in his schoolwork.

267
00:13:05,679 --> 00:13:06,240
Hold on.

268
00:13:07,519 --> 00:13:08,519
You come whenever you like,

269
00:13:08,519 --> 00:13:09,399
and leave whenever you like.

270
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,279
What do you think this place is?

271
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,759
So what do you want?

272
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:13,960
What do I want?

273
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:17,519
You've got to leave something as collateral.

274
00:13:18,159 --> 00:13:18,960
Teacher Danni,

275
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,480
you're a natural beauty,

276
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:21,639
and you've got real potential.

277
00:13:22,039 --> 00:13:24,039
Why don't you stay instead?

278
00:13:29,679 --> 00:13:30,879
You're in big trouble now.

279
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:32,240
Teacher Danni,

280
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,679
this is Disorderly conduct.

281
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:37,799
That slap of yours really hurt.

282
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:39,879
Xiao Qi!

283
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:41,200
Let go of me!

284
00:13:41,399 --> 00:13:42,960
What are you doing? Let go of me!

285
00:13:43,799 --> 00:13:45,000
Go back and tell Wang Xiang,

286
00:13:45,039 --> 00:13:45,720
